snippet.textDisplay:
Ok coming from a guy who has work at MOD pizza for 3-4 ish years. Here’s where you guys went wrong,

1) yes is meant to be a gaint pizza but what you should have done is make a the whole crust should be around 1/2 of the size of the entrance

2) the temperature is to high. Normally it’s best to have it around 450-500 degrees F MAX! Other wise the edges will burn before the cheese is even melted

3) the wooden lifts you are using are simply to big, I’d recommend metal/stainless steal or aluminum ones, easier to use and control even with large pizzas

(trust me I know me and other coworkers put like 3-4 glops if dough together and cooked it in a smaller oven then you guys had)

But In all honesty, you guys really did do a great video, good job to everyone that worked on it! It was joy full and entertaining and I just can’t bring myself to dislike it because of the poor pizza craftsmen ship. I’m studying to work in television and maybe one day I’ll be able to meet you guys! Thanks again for providing an enjoyable 12 min video! I look forward to seeing more for you guys!
snippet.textOriginal:
Ok coming from a guy who has work at MOD pizza for 3-4 ish years. Here’s where you guys went wrong, 

1) yes is meant to be a gaint pizza but what you should have done is make a the whole crust should be around 1/2 of the size of the entrance 

2) the temperature is to high. Normally it’s best to have it around 450-500 degrees F MAX! Other wise the edges will burn before the cheese is even melted

3) the wooden lifts you are using are simply to big, I’d recommend metal/stainless steal or aluminum ones, easier to use and control even with large pizzas 

(trust me I know me and other coworkers put like 3-4 glops if dough together and cooked it in a smaller oven then you guys had)

But In all honesty, you guys really did do a great video, good job to everyone that worked on it! It was joy full and entertaining and I just can’t bring myself to dislike it because of the poor pizza craftsmen ship. I’m studying to work in television and maybe one day I’ll be able to meet you guys! Thanks again for providing an enjoyable 12 min video! I look forward to seeing more for you guys!
